<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-11-13T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-11-13T13:00:00-05:00" n="331" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.00/859: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reber</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-13T13:00:00-05:00">November 13, 1930—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>100. Your 155, November 12, noon. Your proposed action is approved.
                            President King’s reply and attitude in this connection should be
                            immediately reported.</p>
                        <p>The Liberian Consul General at Baltimore will be summoned on November 17
                            to the Department to be questioned by me respecting these reports. This
                            is for your information and is not to be imparted to President King.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>